30 // Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
31 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
32 // the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
33 // static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
34 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
35 #if defined(BUILDING_V8_SHARED) && defined(USING_V8_SHARED)
36 #error both BUILDING_V8_SHARED and USING_V8_SHARED are set - please check the\
37  build configuration to ensure that at most one of these is set
38 #endif
39 
40 #ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
41 # define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
42 #elif USING_V8_SHARED
43 # define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
44 #else
45 # define V8_EXPORT
46 #endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
47 
48 #else // V8_OS_WIN
49 
50 // Setup for Linux shared library export.
51 #if V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_VISIBILITY && defined(V8_SHARED)
52 # ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
53 # define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
54 # else
55 # define V8_EXPORT
56 # endif
57 #else
58 # define V8_EXPORT
59 #endif
60 
61 #endif // V8_OS_WIN

155 class UniqueId {
156  public:
157  explicit UniqueId(intptr_t data)
158  : data_(data) {}
159 
160  bool operator==(const UniqueId& other) const {
161  return data_ == other.data_;
162  }
163 
164  bool operator!=(const UniqueId& other) const {
165  return data_ != other.data_;
166  }
167 
168  bool operator<(const UniqueId& other) const {
169  return data_ < other.data_;
170  }
171 
172  private:
173  intptr_t data_;
174 };

178 #define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
179  while (false) { \

209 template <class T>
210 class Local {
211  public:
212  V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
213  template <class S>
214  V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
215  : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
221  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
222  }
223 
227  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
228 
232  V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
233 
234  V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
235 
236  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
237 
244  template <class S>
245  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
246  internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
247  internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
248  if (a == 0) return b == 0;
249  if (b == 0) return false;
250  return *a == *b;
251  }
252 
253  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
254  const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
255  internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
256  internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
257  if (a == 0) return b == 0;
258  if (b == 0) return false;
259  return *a == *b;
260  }
261 
268  template <class S>
269  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
270  return !operator==(that);
271  }
272 
273  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
274  const Persistent<S>& that) const {
275  return !operator==(that);
276  }
277 
278  template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
279 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
280  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
281  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
282  if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
283 #endif
284  return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
285  }
286 
287 
288  template <class S> V8_INLINE Local<S> As() {
289  return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
290  }
291 
297  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
298  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
299  const PersistentBase<T>& that);
300 
301  private:
302  friend class Utils;
303  template<class F> friend class Eternal;
304  template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
305  template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
306  template<class F> friend class Local;
307  template <class F>
308  friend class MaybeLocal;
309  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
310  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
311  friend class String;
312  friend class Object;
313  friend class Context;
314  template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
315  friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
316  friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);

319  friend class HandleScope;

321  template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
322  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
323  template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;

325  template <class S>
326  V8_INLINE Local(S* that)
327  : val_(that) {}
328  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
329  T* val_;
330 };

350 template <class T>
351 class MaybeLocal {
352  public:
353  V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
354  template <class S>
355  V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
356  : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
357  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
358  }
359 
360  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
361 
362  template <class S>
363  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
364  out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
365  return !IsEmpty();
366  }
367 
368  // Will crash if the MaybeLocal<> is empty.
369  V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
370 
371  template <class S>
372  V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
373  return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
374  }
375 
376  private:
377  T* val_;
378 };

381 // Eternal handles are set-once handles that live for the life of the isolate.
382 template <class T> class Eternal {
383  public:
384  V8_INLINE Eternal() : index_(kInitialValue) { }
385  template<class S>
386  V8_INLINE Eternal(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) : index_(kInitialValue) {
387  Set(isolate, handle);
388  }
389  // Can only be safely called if already set.
390  V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate);
391  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() { return index_ == kInitialValue; }
392  template<class S> V8_INLINE void Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle);
393 
394  private:
395  static const int kInitialValue = -1;
396  int index_;
397 };

400 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
401 
402 
403 template <typename T>
404 class WeakCallbackInfo {
405  public:
406  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
407 
408  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
409  void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
410  Callback* callback)
411  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
412  for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
413  internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
414  }
415  }
416 
417  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
418  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
419  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
420 
421  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("use indexed version",
422  void* GetInternalField1() const) {
423  return internal_fields_[0];
424  }
425  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("use indexed version",
426  void* GetInternalField2() const) {
427  return internal_fields_[1];
428  }
429 
430  bool IsFirstPass() const { return callback_ != nullptr; }
431 
432  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
433  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
434  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
435  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
436  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
437  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
438  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
439 
440  private:
441  Isolate* isolate_;
442  T* parameter_;
443  Callback* callback_;
444  void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
445 };

449 class WeakCallbackData {
450  public:
451  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackData<T, P>& data);

453  WeakCallbackData(Isolate* isolate, P* parameter, Local<T> handle)

455 
456  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
457  V8_INLINE P* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
458  V8_INLINE Local<T> GetValue() const { return handle_; }
459 
460  private:
461  Isolate* isolate_;
462  P* parameter_;
463  Local<T> handle_;
464 };

515  internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
516  if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;

524  internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
525  if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;

527  return *a == *b;
528  }

547  template <typename P>
548  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON(
549  "use WeakCallbackInfo version",
550  void SetWeak(P* parameter,
551  typename WeakCallbackData<T, P>::Callback callback));
552 
553  template <typename S, typename P>
554  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON(
555  "use WeakCallbackInfo version",
556  void SetWeak(P* parameter,
557  typename WeakCallbackData<S, P>::Callback callback));
558 
559  // Phantom persistents work like weak persistents, except that the pointer to
560  // the object being collected is not available in the finalization callback.
561  // This enables the garbage collector to collect the object and any objects
562  // it references transitively in one GC cycle. At the moment you can either
563  // specify a parameter for the callback or the location of two internal
564  // fields in the dying object.
565  template <typename P>
566  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON(
567  "use SetWeak",
568  void SetPhantom(P* parameter,
569  typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
570  int internal_field_index1 = -1,
571  int internal_field_index2 = -1));
572 
573  template <typename P>
574  V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
575  typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
576  WeakCallbackType type);
577 
578  template<typename P>
579  V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
580 
581  // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
582  V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }
583

692 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
693  public:
697  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
703  template <class S>
704  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
705  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
706  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
707  }
713  template <class S, class M2>
714  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
715  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
716  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
717  }
724  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
725  Copy(that);
726  }
727  template <class S, class M2>
728  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
729  Copy(that);
730  }
731  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
732  Copy(that);
733  return *this;
734  }
735  template <class S, class M2>
736  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
737  Copy(that);
738  return *this;
739  }
745  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
746  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
747  }
748 
749  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
750  template <class S>
751  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
752 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
753  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
754  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
755  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
756 #endif
757  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(that);
758  }
759 
760  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
761  template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() { // NOLINT
762  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
763  }
764 
765  private:
766  friend class Isolate;
767  friend class Utils;
768  template<class F> friend class Local;
769  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
770  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
771 
772  template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent(S* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) { }
773  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
774  template<class S, class M2>
775  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
776 };

784 template <class T>
785 class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
786  public:
790  V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
796  template <class S>
797  V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
798  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
799  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
800  }
806  template <class S>
807  V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
808  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
809  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
810  }
814  V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) {
815  other.val_ = nullptr;
816  }
817  V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
821  template <class S>
822  V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
823  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
824  if (this != &rhs) {
825  this->Reset();
826  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
827  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
828  }
829  return *this;
830  }
834  Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); }
835 
836  /*
837  * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
838  */
839  typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
840 
841  private:
842  template <class F>
843  friend class ReturnValue;
844  Global(Global&) = delete;
845  void operator=(Global&) = delete;
846  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
847 };

941  // Make it hard to create heap-allocated or illegal handle scopes by
942  // disallowing certain operations.
943  EscapableHandleScope(const EscapableHandleScope&);
944  void operator=(const EscapableHandleScope&);
945  void* operator new(size_t size);
946  void operator delete(void*, size_t);
947 
948  internal::Object** escape_slot_;
949 };

985 class ScriptOriginOptions {
986  public:
987  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_embedder_debug_script = false,
988  bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
989  bool is_opaque = false)
990  : flags_((is_embedder_debug_script ? kIsEmbedderDebugScript : 0) |
991  (is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
992  (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0)) {}
993  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
994  : flags_(flags &
995  (kIsEmbedderDebugScript | kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque)) {}
996  bool IsEmbedderDebugScript() const {
997  return (flags_ & kIsEmbedderDebugScript) != 0;
998  }
999  bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1000  return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1001  }
1002  bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1003  int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1004 
1005  private:
1006  enum {
1007  kIsEmbedderDebugScript = 1,
1008  kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1 << 1,
1009  kIsOpaque = 1 << 2
1010  };
1011  const int flags_;
1012 };

1124 class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1125  public:
1133  struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1134  enum BufferPolicy {
1135  BufferNotOwned,
1136  BufferOwned
1137  };
1138 
1139  CachedData()
1140  : data(NULL),
1141  length(0),
1142  rejected(false),
1143  buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1144 
1145  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1146  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1147  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1148  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1149  CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1150  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1151  ~CachedData();
1152  // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1153  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1154  const uint8_t* data;
1155  int length;
1156  bool rejected;
1157  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1158 
1159  private:
1160  // Prevent copying. Not implemented.
1161  CachedData(const CachedData&);
1162  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&);
1163  };
1164 
1168  class Source {
1169  public:
1170  // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1171  V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1172  CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1173  V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1174  CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1175  V8_INLINE ~Source();
1176 
1177  // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1178  // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1179  // alive.
1180  V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1181 
1182  private:
1183  friend class ScriptCompiler;
1184  // Prevent copying. Not implemented.
1185  Source(const Source&);
1186  Source& operator=(const Source&);
1187 
1188  Local<String> source_string;
1189 
1190  // Origin information
1191  Local<Value> resource_name;
1192  Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1193  Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1194  ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1195  Local<Value> source_map_url;
1196 
1197  // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1198  // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1199  // set when calling a compile method.
1200  CachedData* cached_data;
1201  };

2081 class V8_EXPORT String : public Name {
2082  public:

2106  bool IsOneByte() const;

2139  enum WriteOptions {
2140  NO_OPTIONS = 0,
2141  HINT_MANY_WRITES_EXPECTED = 1,
2142  NO_NULL_TERMINATION = 2,
2143  PRESERVE_ONE_BYTE_NULL = 4,
2144  // Used by WriteUtf8 to replace orphan surrogate code units with the
2145  // unicode replacement character. Needs to be set to guarantee valid UTF-8
2146  // output.
2147  REPLACE_INVALID_UTF8 = 8
2148  };
2149 
2150  // 16-bit character codes.
2151  int Write(uint16_t* buffer,
2152  int start = 0,
2153  int length = -1,

2447 class V8_EXPORT Symbol : public Name {
2448  public:

2450  Local<Value> Name() const;
2451 
2452  // Create a symbol. If name is not empty, it will be used as the description.
2453  static Local<Symbol> New(
2454  Isolate *isolate, Local<String> name = Local<String>());
2455 
2456  // Access global symbol registry.
2457  // Note that symbols created this way are never collected, so
2458  // they should only be used for statically fixed properties.
2459  // Also, there is only one global name space for the names used as keys.
2460  // To minimize the potential for clashes, use qualified names as keys.
2461  static Local<Symbol> For(Isolate *isolate, Local<String> name);
2462 
2463  // Retrieve a global symbol. Similar to |For|, but using a separate
2464  // registry that is not accessible by (and cannot clash with) JavaScript code.
2465  static Local<Symbol> ForApi(Isolate *isolate, Local<String> name);
2466 
2467  // Well-known symbols
2468  static Local<Symbol> GetIterator(Isolate* isolate);
2469  static Local<Symbol> GetUnscopables(Isolate* isolate);
2470  static Local<Symbol> GetToStringTag(Isolate* isolate);
2471 
2472  V8_INLINE static Symbol* Cast(v8::Value* obj);
2473 
2474  private:
2475  Symbol();
2476  static void CheckCast(v8::Value* obj);
2477 };

3056 
3057 template<typename T>
3058 class ReturnValue {
3059  public:
3060  template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3061  : value_(that.value_) {
3062  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3063  }
3064  // Local setters
3065  template <typename S>
3066  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Global<> instead",
3067  void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3068  template <typename S>
3069  V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3070  template <typename S>
3071  V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3072  // Fast primitive setters
3073  V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3074  V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3075  V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3076  V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3077  // Fast JS primitive setters
3078  V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3079  V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3080  V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3081  // Convenience getter for Isolate
3082  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate();
3083 
3084  // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3085  template <typename S>
3086  V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3087 
3088  private:
3089  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3090  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;

5084 struct JitCodeEvent {
5085  enum EventType {
5086  CODE_ADDED,
5087  CODE_MOVED,
5088  CODE_REMOVED,
5089  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
5090  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
5091  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
5092  };
5093  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
5094  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
5095  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
5096  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
5097  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
5098  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
5099 
5100  // Type of event.
5101  EventType type;
5102  // Start of the instructions.
5103  void* code_start;
5104  // Size of the instructions.
5105  size_t code_len;
5106  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
5107  Local<UnboundScript> script;
5108  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
5109  // code line information which is returned from the
5110  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
5111  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
5112  void* user_data;
5113 
5114  struct name_t {
5115  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
5116  // zero-terminated.
5117  const char* str;
5118  // Number of chars in str.
5119  size_t len;
5120  };
5121 
5122  struct line_info_t {
5123  // PC offset
5124  size_t offset;
5125  // Code postion
5126  size_t pos;
5127  // The position type.
5128  PositionType position_type;
5129  };
5130 
5131  union {
5132  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
5133  struct name_t name;
5134 
5135  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
5136  struct line_info_t line_info;
5137 
5138  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
5139  void* new_code_start;
5140  };
5141 };

6333 template <class T>
6334 class Maybe {
6335  public:
6336  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value; }
6337  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value; }
6338 
6339  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6340  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
6341  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
6342  return value;
6343  }
6344 
6345  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
6346  return has_value ? value : default_value;
6347  }
6348 
6349  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
6350  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
6351  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
6352  }
6353 
6354  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
6355  return !operator==(other);
6356  }
6357 
6358  private:
6359  Maybe() : has_value(false) {}
6360  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value(true), value(t) {}
6361 
6362  bool has_value;
6363  T value;
6364 
6365  template <class U>
6366  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
6367  template <class U>
6368  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
6369 };
6370 
6371 
6372 template <class T>
6373 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
6374  return Maybe<T>();
6375 }
6376 
6377 
6378 template <class T>
6379 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
6380  return Maybe<T>(t);
6381 }

6859 // --- Implementation ---
6860 
6861 
6862 namespace internal {
6863 
6864 const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
6865 const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
6866 const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
6867 
6868 // Tag information for HeapObject.
6869 const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
6870 const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
6871 const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
6872 
6873 // Tag information for Smi.
6874 const int kSmiTag = 0;
6875 const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
6876 const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
6877 
6878 template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
6879 
6880 template<int kSmiShiftSize>
6881 V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6882  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6883  uintptr_t tagged_value =
6884  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
6885  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
6886 }
6887 
6888 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
6889 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
6890  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
6891  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
6892  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
6893  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
6894  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6895  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
6896  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
6897  }
6898  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6899  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
6900  }
6901  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
6902  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
6903  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
6904  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
6905  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
6906  //
6907  // CAUTION: The original code below:
6908  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
6909  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
6910  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
6911  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
6912  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
6913  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
6914  }
6915 };
6916 
6917 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
6918 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
6919  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
6920  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
6921  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
6922  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
6923  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6924  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
6925  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
6926  }
6927  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6928  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
6929  }
6930  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
6931  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
6932  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
6933  }
6934 };
6935 
6936 typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
6937 const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
6938 const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
6939 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
6940 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }
6941 
6947 class Internals {
6948  public:
6949  // These values match non-compiler-dependent values defined within
6950  // the implementation of v8.
6951  static const int kHeapObjectMapOffset = 0;
6952  static const int kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset =
6953  1 * kApiPointerSize + kApiIntSize;
6954  static const int kStringResourceOffset = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
6955 
6956  static const int kOddballKindOffset = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
6957  static const int kForeignAddressOffset = kApiPointerSize;
6958  static const int kJSObjectHeaderSize = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
6959  static const int kFixedArrayHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
6960  static const int kContextHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
6961  static const int kContextEmbedderDataIndex = 81;
6962  static const int kFullStringRepresentationMask = 0x07;
6963  static const int kStringEncodingMask = 0x4;
6964  static const int kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag = 0x02;
6965  static const int kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag = 0x06;
6966 
6967  static const int kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset = 0 * kApiPointerSize;
6968  static const int kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryOffset =
6969  4 * kApiPointerSize;
6970  static const int kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryAtLastGlobalGCOffset =
6971  kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryOffset + kApiInt64Size;
6972  static const int kIsolateRootsOffset =
6973  kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryAtLastGlobalGCOffset + kApiInt64Size +
6974  kApiPointerSize;
6975  static const int kUndefinedValueRootIndex = 5;
6976  static const int kNullValueRootIndex = 7;
6977  static const int kTrueValueRootIndex = 8;
6978  static const int kFalseValueRootIndex = 9;
6979  static const int kEmptyStringRootIndex = 10;
6980 
6981  // The external allocation limit should be below 256 MB on all architectures
6982  // to avoid that resource-constrained embedders run low on memory.
6983  static const int kExternalAllocationLimit = 192 * 1024 * 1024;
6984 
6985  static const int kNodeClassIdOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize;
6986  static const int kNodeFlagsOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize + 3;
6987  static const int kNodeStateMask = 0x7;
6988  static const int kNodeStateIsWeakValue = 2;
6989  static const int kNodeStateIsPendingValue = 3;
6990  static const int kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue = 4;
6991  static const int kNodeIsIndependentShift = 3;
6992  static const int kNodeIsPartiallyDependentShift = 4;
6993 
6994  static const int kJSObjectType = 0xbe;
6995  static const int kFirstNonstringType = 0x80;
6996  static const int kOddballType = 0x83;
6997  static const int kForeignType = 0x87;
6998 
6999  static const int kUndefinedOddballKind = 5;
7000  static const int kNullOddballKind = 3;
7001 
7002  static const uint32_t kNumIsolateDataSlots = 4;
7003 
7004  V8_EXPORT static void CheckInitializedImpl(v8::Isolate* isolate);
7005  V8_INLINE static void CheckInitialized(v8::Isolate* isolate) {
7006 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7007  CheckInitializedImpl(isolate);
7008 #endif
7009  }

7011  V8_INLINE static bool HasHeapObjectTag(const internal::Object* value) {
7012  return ((reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) & kHeapObjectTagMask) ==
7013  kHeapObjectTag);
7014  }
7015 
7016  V8_INLINE static int SmiValue(const internal::Object* value) {
7017  return PlatformSmiTagging::SmiToInt(value);
7018  }
7019 
7020  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7021  return PlatformSmiTagging::IntToSmi(value);
7022  }

7025  return PlatformSmiTagging::IsValidSmi(value);
7026  }

7028  V8_INLINE static int GetInstanceType(const internal::Object* obj) {
7029  typedef internal::Object O;
7030  O* map = ReadField<O*>(obj, kHeapObjectMapOffset);
7031  // Map::InstanceType is defined so that it will always be loaded into
7032  // the LS 8 bits of one 16-bit word, regardless of endianess.
7033  return ReadField<uint16_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset) & 0xff;
7034  }
7035 
7036  V8_INLINE static int GetOddballKind(const internal::Object* obj) {
7037  typedef internal::Object O;
7038  return SmiValue(ReadField<O*>(obj, kOddballKindOffset));
7039  }
7040 
7041  V8_INLINE static bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {
7042  int representation = (instance_type & kFullStringRepresentationMask);
7043  return representation == kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag;
7044  }
7045 
7046  V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
7047  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7048  return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
7049  }
7050 
7051  V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
7052  bool value, int shift) {
7053  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7054  uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
7055  *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
7056  }
7057 
7058  V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {
7059  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7060  return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
7061  }
7062 
7063  V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
7064  uint8_t value) {
7065  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7066  *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
7067  }
7068 
7069  V8_INLINE static void SetEmbedderData(v8::Isolate* isolate,
7070  uint32_t slot,
7071  void* data) {
7072  uint8_t *addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t *>(isolate) +
7073  kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
7074  *reinterpret_cast<void**>(addr) = data;
7075  }
7076 
7077  V8_INLINE static void* GetEmbedderData(const v8::Isolate* isolate,
7078  uint32_t slot) {
7079  const uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(isolate) +
7080  kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
7081  return *reinterpret_cast<void* const*>(addr);
7082  }
7083 
7084  V8_INLINE static internal::Object** GetRoot(v8::Isolate* isolate,
7085  int index) {
7086  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) + kIsolateRootsOffset;
7087  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(addr + index * kApiPointerSize);
7088  }
7089 
7090  template <typename T>
7091  V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
7092  const uint8_t* addr =
7093  reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
7094  return *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(addr);
7095  }
7096 
7097  template <typename T>
7098  V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
7099  typedef internal::Object O;
7100  typedef internal::Internals I;
7101  O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
7102  int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
7103  (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
7104  O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
7105  int value_offset =
7106  I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7107  return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
7108  }
7109 };
7110 
7111 } // namespace internal

7177 template <class T, class M>
7178 template <class S, class M2>
7179 void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
7180  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
7181  this->Reset();
7182  if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
7183  internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
7184  this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
7185  M::Copy(that, this);
7186 }

7189 template <class T>
7190 bool PersistentBase<T>::IsIndependent() const {
7191  typedef internal::Internals I;
7192  if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
7193  return I::GetNodeFlag(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_),
7194  I::kNodeIsIndependentShift);
7195 }

7198 template <class T>
7199 bool PersistentBase<T>::IsNearDeath() const {
7200  typedef internal::Internals I;
7201  if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
7202  uint8_t node_state =
7203  I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
7204  return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
7205  node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
7206 }

7213  return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_)) ==
7214  I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
7215 }

7381 template<typename T>

7383  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
7384  typedef internal::Internals I;
7385  if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
7386  *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
7387  return;
7388  }

7392 template<typename T>
7393 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
7394  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
7395  // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
7396  bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
7397  if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
7398  Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
7399  return;
7400  }
7401  Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
7402 }
7403 
7404 template<typename T>
7405 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
7406  TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
7407  typedef internal::Internals I;
7408  int root_index;
7409  if (value) {
7410  root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
7411  } else {
7412  root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
7413  }
7414  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
7415 }

7420  typedef internal::Internals I;
7421  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
7422 }

7429 }

7600 
7601 
7602 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
7603 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7604  typedef internal::Object O;
7605  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
7606  typedef internal::Internals I;
7607  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
7608  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
7609  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
7610  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType) {
7611  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7612  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
7613  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
7614  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
7615  }
7616 #endif
7617  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
7618 }
7619 
7620 
7621 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
7622 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7623  typedef internal::Object O;
7624  typedef internal::Internals I;
7625  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
7626  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
7627  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
7628  if (V8_LIKELY(I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType)) {
7629  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7630  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
7631  }
7632 #endif
7633  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
7634 }

7653 
7654 String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
7655  typedef internal::Object O;
7656  typedef internal::Internals I;
7657  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
7658  String::ExternalStringResource* result;
7659  if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
7660  void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
7661  result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
7662  } else {
7663  result = NULL;
7664  }
7665 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7666  VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
7667 #endif
7668  return result;
7669 }
7670 
7671 
7672 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
7673  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
7674  typedef internal::Object O;
7675  typedef internal::Internals I;
7676  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
7677  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
7678  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
7679  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
7680  if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
7681  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
7682  void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
7683  resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
7684  }
7685 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7686  VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
7687 #endif
7688  return resource;
7689 }

7700 bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
7701  typedef internal::Object O;
7702  typedef internal::Internals I;
7703  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
7704  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
7705  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
7706  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
7707 }

8161 
8162 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
8163  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
8164  typedef internal::Internals I;
8165  int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory =
8166  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8167  I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryOffset);
8168  int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc =
8169  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
8170  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8171  I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryAtLastGlobalGCOffset);
8172  int64_t amount = *amount_of_external_allocated_memory + change_in_bytes;
8173  if (change_in_bytes > 0 &&
8174  amount - *amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc >
8175  I::kExternalAllocationLimit) {
8176  CollectAllGarbage("external memory allocation limit reached.");
8177  }
8178  *amount_of_external_allocated_memory = amount;
8179  return *amount_of_external_allocated_memory;
8180 }

8210 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
8211 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8212  typedef internal::Object O;
8213  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
8214  typedef internal::Internals I;
8215  HO* context = *reinterpret_cast<HO**>(this);
8216  O** result =
8217  HandleScope::CreateHandle(context, I::ReadEmbedderData<O*>(this, index));
8218  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
8219 #else
8220  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
8221 #endif
8222 }
